Severity,Vulnerability Type,File Path,Description,Recommended Remediation
Critical,Broken Authentication (Missing Checks),backend/server.js,All data endpoints (profiles, weekly trends, moods) are fully exposed without token verification checks.,Implement a middleware (e.g. verifying JWTs) and apply it to protect all data endpoints.
Critical,Insecure Direct Object Reference (IDOR),backend/server.js,Endpoints like /api/user/profile/:userId allow any client to fetch or overwrite any user profile by altering the ID in the URL.,Resolve the user identity from the verified server-side session/token rather than trusting URL parameters.
High,Weak Authentication (Plaintext Passwords),backend/server.js,User credentials in /api/auth/signup are processed and stored in-memory as plaintext without hashing.,Use a library like bcrypt or argon2 to hash passwords before comparison or storage.
High,Predictable Session Tokens,backend/server.js,The server returns a hardcoded mock token ("mock-jwt-token-777") for all users.,Use a library like jsonwebtoken to dynamically sign and verify cryptographically strong tokens.
Medium,CORS Wildcard Configuration,backend/server.js,The server configures app.use(cors()) which allows wildcard access (Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *) from any domain.,Restrict CORS settings to explicitly whitelist only your application's domain.
Medium,Missing Input Sanitization & Validation,backend/server.js,Incoming request bodies (like user notes, email, and metadata) are consumed directly without schema validation.,Integrate validation schema libraries like joi or zod to validate type, size, and character properties.
